China's Largest Companies Unite Against Alibaba
Chinese companies, including China’s largest commercial real estate developer Dalian Wanda Group and internet giants Tencent Holdings (social networks, messenger, etc.) and Baidu (China’s largest search engine), are creating a company that will compete with Ali’s online market.
However, achieving the miracle of the Chinese Internet, which has left even its American rivals – eBay and Amazon.com, will not be easy.
Union of the Largest
The companies plan to invest 5 billion yuan ($814 million) in the joint venture, 70% of which will be owned by Wanda and 15% - each of the Internet companies, according to the report.
